🧬 Medical & Healthcare
Averna – Precision Embroidery for Medical Research
Client: Averna, medical research company.


Goal: Embroidered North Face jackets that reflected the company’s precision and premium image.


Challenge: Their logo included extremely fine details, including a 1-inch DNA helix. A previous vendor failed, saying “this is the best we can do.”


Solution: Adjusted stitch density, used thinner thread and specialized needles, ran multiple test samples, and fine-tuned machine tension to prevent thread breaks and achieve crisp embroidery.


Result: Client was thrilled and called the work “perfect.” Even the CEO, who was highly particular, was satisfied. The client continues to order more projects and has referred Joe to others.


Key Message: Joe’s team delivers precision and quality in branding, matching even the highest client standards.


