Case Study: Thornton & Grooms
Client: Thornton & Grooms, one of Michigan’s largest HVAC and plumbing companies
 Industry: Home Services
Goal
 Thornton & Grooms needed a single, reliable partner to manage all their branded apparel and promotional needs. They had been juggling multiple vendors and wanted a simple, predictable, all-in-one solution that made ordering easy for both management and staff.
Challenge
 Before working with Joe, their process was chaotic:
Quotes didn’t match final invoices, sometimes off by large amounts.


Their team was ordering from cheap online sites, but service and consistency suffered.


Employees were frustrated by hidden costs and confusing online checkout experiences.


When issues came up, no one knew which vendor handled what, or how to fix it quickly.


Solution
 Joe’s team created a completely custom webstore designed specifically around Thornton & Grooms’ internal needs:
Transparent pricing: “What you see is what you pay.” No add-ons, no surprises.


Centralized management: One place for everything — apparel, jackets, beanies, promo gear — with Joe’s team as the single point of contact.


Accurate quoting & predictable delivery: Orders are billed live as they’re placed, eliminating the need for large prepaid balances (saving them $10–20K in tied-up funds).


Employee engagement: Created a jacket store where employees could try on real samples for size and color before ordering, making the process hands-on and fun.


Responsive partnership: Fast, professional communication; issues handled immediately and proactively.


Result
Dramatic reduction in order errors and fulfillment confusion.


Increased employee participation in webstore programs.


Managers consistently send positive internal reviews for responsiveness and accuracy.


Management team fully trusts the system — they know any issue will be handled quickly and correctly.


Thornton & Grooms now sees Joe’s team as an extension of their own staff, not just a vendor.


Key Message
 Joe provides custom, turnkey uniform and merch programs that simplify ordering, eliminate headaches, and make large organizations feel like everything “just works.” Thornton & Grooms went from chasing vendors to having a trusted partner who runs their program like part of their team.

